1) Install CCL (Clozure Common Lisp).

o  Download CCL from an appropriate directory.
	svn co http://svn.clozure.com/publicsvn/openmcl/release/1.5/<version>/ccl
	where <version> is one of linuxx86, freebsdx86, solarisx86, windows, darwinppc, or linuxppc.

o  Copy ccl/scripts/ccl or ccl/scripts/ccl64 to somewhere in your PATH.

o  Set the variable CCL_DEFAULT_DIRECTORY to the path to CCL (not ending the path with a /).


2) Install minisat (if using ESODatalog) and SNARK (if using Plato)

o  Minisat
	http://minisat.se/downloads/minisat-2.2.0.tar.gz

o  SNARK
	http://www.ai.sri.com/~stickel/snark.tar.gz	


3) Customize and compile application

	cd /to/path/with/clicl
	Change clicl-init.lisp to include one or both of the following lines
		(setq *minisat* "/path/to/minisat")
		(setq *snark-path* "/path/to/snark/")	
	make


4) Run
	
	./clicl

Note: clicl first starts by executing the Lisp file clicl-init.lisp, so any changes made there will be reflected each time clicl is started.


5) Quit

	1> (quit)
	? (quit)

